clinical_study.brief_title: A Study to Assess the Safety and Efficacy of AZD2936 in Participants With Advanced or Metastatic Non-small Cell Lung Cancer (NSCLC)
clinical_study.official_title: A Phase I/II, Open-label, Dose Escalation and Dose Expansion Study to Evaluate the Safety, Pharmacokinetics, Pharmacodynamics, and Efficacy of AZD2936 Anti-TIGIT/Anti-PD-1 Bispecific Antibody in Participants With Advanced or Metastatic Non-small Cell Lung Cancer

brief_summary.textblock: This is a Phase I/II study designed to evaluate if experimental anti-TIGIT/anti-PD-1 bispecific antibody, AZD2936 is safe, tolerable and efficacious in participants with Advanced or Metastatic Non-small Cell Lung Cancer.

detailed_description.textblock: This is a first-time-in-human (FTIH), open-label, multicenter, multi-part, dose-escalation and dose-expansion study to evaluate the safety, pharmacokinetics (PK), pharmacodynamics, and efficacy of AZD2936 in adult participants with stage III unresectable or stage IV NSCLC. The study includes 4 parts: Part A (dose escalation) and Parts B-D (dose expansion).

study_design_info.intervention_model_description: The study includes 4 parts: Part A (dose escalation) and Parts B-D (dose expansion).

primary_outcome.measure: Percentage of participants with adverse events (AEs) and immune mediated AEs (imAEs), serious AEs (SAEs), dose limiting toxicities (DLTs), vital signs, and abnormal laboratory parameters
primary_outcome.time_frame: Part A, B, C: From the time of informed consent until 90 days after the last dose of AZD2936
primary_outcome.description: A DLT is a toxicity defined by the study protocol that occurs from the first dose of study intervention up to the end of the DLT evaluation period that is assessed as clearly unrelated to the primary disease or intercurrent illness.

primary_outcome.measure: Rate of AZD2936 discontinuation due to toxicity
primary_outcome.time_frame: Part A, B, C: From first dose to the last dose of AZD2936 (an average of 6 months)
primary_outcome.description: Percentage of participants with AEs leading to discontinuation of AZD2936

primary_outcome.time_frame: Part B, C: From first dose of AZD2936 to progressive disease or death in the absence of disease progression (approximately 2 years)
primary_outcome.description: Percentage of participants with a confirmed Complete Response (CR) or Partial Response (PR) according to RECIST v1.1

secondary_outcome.time_frame: Part A: From first dose of AZD2936 to progressive disease or death in the absence of disease progression (approximately 2 years)
secondary_outcome.description: Percentage of participants with a confirmed CR or PR according to RECIST v1.1

secondary_outcome.time_frame: Part A, B, C: From first dose of AZD2936 to progressive disease or death in the absence of disease progression (approximately 2 years)
secondary_outcome.description: Percentage of participants who have a best objective response of confirmed CR or PR or who have SD lasting for at least a certain time of period after start of treatment

secondary_outcome.time_frame: Part A, B, C: From first dose of AZD2936 to progressive disease or death in the absence of disease progression (approximately 2 years)
secondary_outcome.description: The time from first response according to RECIST v1.1 until progression or death in the absence of disease progression

secondary_outcome.time_frame: Part A, B, C: From first dose of AZD2936 to progressive disease or death in the absence of disease progression (approximately 2 years)
secondary_outcome.description: The percentage of participants according to RECIST v1.1 with a confirmed CR or PR lasting 6 months or more

secondary_outcome.time_frame: Part B, C: From first dose of AZD2936 to progressive disease or death in the absence of disease progression. (approximately 2 years)

criteria.textblock:
Inclusion Criteria:
- Written informed consent
- Aged 18 or above
- Unresectable stage III or stage IV squamous or non-squamous NSCLC not amenable to curative surgery or radiation.
- Documented PD-L1 expression by PD-L1 IHC per local report.
- Confirmed progression during treatment with a CPI-including regimen.
- ECOG performance status of 0 or 1 at enrolment.
- Life expectancy of ≥ 12 weeks at enrolment.
- Adequate bone marrow, liver and kidney function
Exclusion Criteria:
- Sensitizing epidermal growth factor receptor (EGFR) mutations or anaplastic lymphoma kinase (ALK) fusion
- Documented test result for any other known genomic alteration for which a targeted therapy is approved in first line per local standard of care (e.g. ROS1, NTRK fusions, BRAF, V600E mutation)
- Previous treatment with an anti-TIGIT therapy
- Any concurrent chemotherapy, radiotherapy, investigational, biologic, or hormonal therapy for cancer treatment.
- Primary or secondary resistance after treatment with 2 or more regimens including a CPI.
- Symptomatic central nervous system (CNS) metastasis.
- Thromboembolic event within 3 months prior to enrolment.
- Other invasive malignancy within 2 years prior to screening.
